title: MusicNews | Listen: This Fall Out Boy cover of a song from The Jungle Book might ruin your childhood
text:
If you're of a certain age - or indeed, of any generation, considering it was released in 1967 - the classic Disney film ' The Jungle Book ' probably holds very fond memories for you.
The songs in the film are particularly memorable - not least the tune sung by King Louie, 'I Wan'na Be Like You (The Monkey Song)'. The vocals on the original were provided by the legendary Louis Prima , but now Fall Out Boy have put their own take on it, complete with guitar solos.
Pete Wentz and co. covered the song for a forthcoming 'We Love Disney ' compilation that also features the likes of Jessie Ware, Ne-Yo and Gwen Stefani, all covering songs from Disney movies.
Depending on your feelings on Fall Out Boy, however, the below track might ruin your childhood memories of the film.
